column1: A lot of E. milfoil on surface of water in a few areas (bet. Kramer pier + peninsula- bet. cabin + island- in front of hermitage). Lake has an unusual yellow green murky hue not seen in the past.  Quite a bit of Decayed Organic Plant Material chunks floating on surface.
Water in Bark River upstream much clearer than lake.

column2: Two great blue herons on lake. Some lily pads in bloom. Spots of weeds floating on lake surface (out from R. pier- Retreat center bay). Lake color is better (more green- less yellow) and clearer. The previous week was much cooler temperatures (70s during the day and 50s at night).
Surface weeds between cabin + K. property- K. bay and Retreat Center pier

column1: Warm weather the previous weed (more algae present)

column2: Many lily pads on south end of lake- a lot of Decayed Organic Plant Material floating throughout the lake especially from the river inlet to north end of lake. Areas of weeds floating on surface still present between Retreat Center + island and also small area west of K. pier.
Sunny- pretty calm- Lake is green/yellow in color

column1: Blobs of bright green algae seen forming on the SW end of lake near shoreline - spirogyra

The lake bottom near the Bark River inlet and outlet is covered with bright green algae (spirogyra) not seen on this lake in the past with the exception of last summer after effluent from Dela-Hart entered river.
Canada geese nesting on island- Great Blue heron spotted on east side of lake- Mallard spotted near island.

column2: Breezy- Sunny- Spirogyra along bed of lake in the river inlet/outlet area

column2: Light breeze- partly cloudy- great blue heron on shoreline.

Spirogyra along lake bottom in the river inlet/outlet area.
Kayakers + canoers out enjoying lake today.

column2: Party cloudy- pretty calm- couple of Canada geese on lake. Also a pair of mallards nesting. Eurasian milfoil growing on south end of lake. Treatment for Eurasian milfoil took place on Tuesday. Kayakers + canoers enjoying lake today.

column1: A few green/brown blobs floating around.
